Yeah im throwing my opinion on format out as well, MP4 and MKV are BOSS! period, end of story, uncompressed AVI is bloated and overweight at best, even compressed AVI is ridiculously huge. Now if your inet provider is like mine and you're limited on bandwidth wouldn't you prefer a smaller download that wont cost you on the bandwidth. 17,000 shows in my collection all RMVB, MKV, M4V and MP4 formats, love them mini player formats. And if you can't play them, you need to go to google school. Get CCCP Codec Pack and use Media Player Classic. Never have any issues and ive seen MKV's put AVI to shame for quality.
